    <note>Liu(2) Liben [13242] At least some of Shi's [1226] sons remained in Linjiang or moved to Jizhou and then back again. I am leaving Liben and his progeny and Liyan [13243] (who may, however, have moved to Suzhou) and his progeny in Linjiang (i.e those for whom there is no direct or indirect evidence of residence in Kaifeng). However Ban's [1220] descendants explicitly moved back to Linjiang at the beginning of Southern Song. (See Liu(2) Guinian's [13247] documentation). Clearly segmentation took place in the generation after Ban, Chang [3580], Qun [13244], Zi(3) [13245] and Du [13252] (all with radical 66 as generation indicator). Linjiang FZ, 12.2a. CBD, 5, 3932.</note>
